rComments: The greatest course I took in university! So informative and the professor did an amazing job at conveying the information during lectures. Was easy to memorize because the material is very interesting. :)

Tests on the most insignificant and small details possible. Makes you watch hour long documentaries and expects you to remember details like the cost of a cab a character took to the hospital. How does that show our knowledge on global health? Doesn't care about her students and gave no time, 120 questions for 120 min on final worth 40%, AVOID.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Really enjoyed this class. it's super interesting and touches on a lot of the world's issues. There is a lot of documentaries which I think are necessary in order to show the real life experiences. I also enjoyed watching videos on my bed instead of hard core studying. Exams are straightforward as long as you watch the videos and go over the slides

Can feel overwhelming and frustrating cuz there is so many videos, documentaries, notes, textbook, articles for every class and midterms are long with long answer, MC, T/F ect... But the material is interesting and everything is related. Exams are straightforward. some questions are who, what, when about the videos just to see if you watched it.

Her powerpoint are so disorganized with random colours everywhere. There are so many videos and readings. I took SSS 2110 with her and she uses all the same videos... concepts and articles seem outdated.  Her tests are extremely long. Make sure you attend class if you want a good mark because she excludes things in lecture on her posted ppts

Worst prof I ever had. Is low key racist and says super inappropriate things that are outdated and "backed up by studies" that are from the previous millenium. One of the only topics she included on Indigenous people was concluding that they "just sniff gas". Just awful.
Worst professor I've ever had. Hard marker and won't explain why you lost marks. Do not take if you want to maintain a high GPA.

I found the material and the way it was presented by professor Edmonds to be very informative and clear, although I think it was a bit redundant when we discussed the mandatory readings in almost the same amount of detail as the reading itself. Professor Edmonds doesn't really engage with her students at all, and we had to ask questions on chat.

I took this class as an elective and am very disappointed by the outcome - prof presents very outdated material and adds to that with her own outdated views. Two midterms and a final all proctored in Zoom and took 4+ weeks for results to come back for each. Textbook is expensive. Also: her slides are unreadable if you're colourblind. Avoid.

I forgot to rate her last year so heres my very late review. Professor Edmonds gives very interesting lectures, shes very accommodating for those who do CSL (I wanted to go in a healthcare profession and she allowed me to do a more hands-on placement so I could gain experience and add to my resume) and shes just very sweet. I highly recommend!

I had Louise for a class in person and I enjoyed that more. She doesn't record lectures and the online lectures can be boring. Class content seemed outdated and irrelevant to aging a lot of the time. She's nice and the open book tests are easy if you take good notes and study. Write down everything, even her random stories.
I really enjoyed Global Health with Prof Edmonds! Her midterms were very straightforward with no tricks. She also gave hints during lectures, so make sure you attend them. Very sweet and reasonable.

Ive had professor Edmonds for 3 courses in my undergrad and honestly she is one of my favourite professors. Yes, she tests on material she may have mentioned once in her lecture that wasnt on the slides, but also the rest of the material is easy so I think this is completely fair. Only complaint is she can be hard to reach outside of lectures.

Shes a sweet woman and shes hilarious. My main complaint is the test content. There were several questions that were about random movies and random celebrities who were briefly mentioned in class or not even discussed in the lectures. The questions on the tests are also very vague. Lectures are easy to follow.
Prof Edmonds is really great! I enjoyed the class a lot. Its super important to attend lectures and take note of her examples.

One of the best profs in health sci! She was so kind, approachable after class, and genuinely wanted to get to know you. She gives out little hints during class for potential questions on the midterms, and is very upfront about exam content and what to expect. She clearly knows her content and is able to convey information really well.

Louise really is a gem. Her material she tests comes from her lecture slides, her discussion and the textbook which is 100% fair. In all of her lectures, she is engaged with the class. As long as you pay attention in class and listen to what she is saying, you will learn valuable material and get a good grade!

Honestly, one of the best profs Ive had at uOttawa! shes so a caring and truly wants the best for her students. If you have the chance, take this prof (ignore the negative reviews, because theyre not true)!!

I love Louise, she's hilarious. 3 hour lectures but I went to every one cause I enjoyed listening to her. 2 midterms and a final-has oddly specific questions on which authors wrote which readings/things she said in class but otherwise super easy. The content is interesting and she can ramble sometimes but tells good stories to help you remember.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: This class was mandatory for my minor, the class material was overall pretty easy but she is a hard marker for no reason. She will pick the littlest things to take marks off of you in order to get you ready for the real world . Would not recommend taking this course with prof Edmonds if you want to keep your GPA high.

one of my favourite profs that i have ever had, lots to memorize but she wants her students to succeed and gives lots of hints. i thought this class was going to be awful but she made it one of my favourite classes i have ever taken. honestly an amazing proff and person i can't put it into words. 100% would recommend her!

Louise's class is pretty interesting and relevant. Her lectures are a bit all over the place, but she's very clear about what you'll be evaluated on. There's 2 midterms and a final, and she tends to drop A LOT of hints in class which are helpful. She wants you to succeed (even changed the final for our class to play to our strengths as a class).

The class taught my Louise Edmonds is a very interesting class. I genuinely l liked the class and it did advance my learning. With that said, it is quite lecture heavy and there is ALOT of material to memorize. Additionally, the exams are quite hard and once again, memorization is emphasized. Assignments included: midterm 1, midterm 2, and final.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Hm. Good luck.

Louise is dismissive to her students. Her lectures are very dry but it is important to show up because her many tangents are tested. Her midterms are deceptively easy but beware on the final because she will ask for every tiny unimportant detail from the lectures and extra readings/videos. Would not recommend taking this course.

Great prof, is available for help via email or in person. Expectations for exams are not super clear, but it's pretty intuitive that the lists will be tested as short answers, and long answers should incorporate concepts and examples from the course. Once you've taken one of her tests, you'll know how all of them will be like.

She said things would be on the final when they weren't. She didn't tell us at all what to expect for the final! She didn't give us any instructions on what she was looking for in her essay questions. I was extremely disappointing with her lack of caring for the class. I would not recommend based on how little she cares about her students.

My 3rd course with Prof Edmonds. Her 2 midterms are very straightforward. Go to lectures, look them over and you'll be fine. She gives away the short answer questions in hints during lectures so go to class! You'll want to attend lecture since she's a great lecturer and makes 3 hour lectures go by quick!

Louise's lectures are so interesting and she has had such an interesting life the hour and a half flew by. It was important to attend because she would test on her anecdotes (course relevant). She assigns readings from journals/websites/videos which she provides in the syllabus and it is important to at least know the authors/names/topics for tests

Her expectations are clear. Many readings but no manual to buy. Everything she presents will be tested in exam so take good notes and study everything (syllabus and all). She is interesting and presents her subject extremely well. This course is a lot of work, but it is worth it.

Probably the worst prof I've ever had. Uniformed and not up to date with current literature. Based her information off of non-academic sources. Gives close to 50 pages of readings per week. Wont let you ask questions during midterms. Also very uneducated about mobility issues and takes it upon herself to label these people as couch potatoes.

This was the best class I have taken at uOttawa. It was always interesting and fun to participate in. The prof is amazing and VERY fair when it comes to the exams. if you go to class and read your notes a couple times before the exam you can do well, but it's helpful if you're an auditory learner. She brings movies and candy some classes too!

One of the most horrible profs I've ever had...  Does not post everything online and expects you to know everything. She even asks uncovered questions in the exam to test your general knowledge... as if I have time to watch the news daily. My lowest grade ...

If you are taking this class for actually getting some knowledge out of it, don't do it. If you are just getting in for an easy A, you are good to go.  I found that while some lectures were interesting (2), most of them were very repetitive and did not actually yield any good. The tests are extremely easy, just memorize presentations the same day.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Amazing professor, I recommend her to everybody. Class was solid, no textbook but weekly readings are absolutely required. There's not much on her slides and she also leaves some out during lectures so you must go to class to get the correct info. Just by sitting and listening you'll get a great mark.

horrible. uOttawa is famous for providing profs that have zero knowledge in the actual course. Pretty sure shes a polisci prof. for a second year elective course, it was my heaviest class. all cumulative. ridiculous testing methods

Really nice prof and a interesting lecturer, she really cares a lot about this subject and it made taking the course really that more interesting. She can be a bit stats heavy on exams but she generally hints at this in class. Know definitions from the textbook and general themes from it as well. No project, fair exams. Taking class again with her
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: A nice professor, course content is really interesting but she asks very obscure questions  on tests from something she said one time during class or a tiny detail from the textbook. Your grade will reflect your ability to memorize, not to understand the material. Also takes a long time to grade tests and respond to emails.

Honestly, she is one of the best teachers I've had! Her way of teaching is amazing, her goals are set and as long as you listen in class, you will easily pass. Her exams are pretty simple (again, if you pay attention). No text books but online readings.  Straight forward! Would love to have her again!

Alright, to simplify things: AVOID HER AT ALL COSTS. Why? Heres a few reasons: 1. she will test you on the same material 3 times, final is cumulative and 50%. 2. you must attend class. she says things that are not on the slide but will be on the exam. 3. Textbook? get ready to memorize all the definitions cover to cover. 4. Gd luck if you have her!

Does not give clear expectations for exams, marking scheme is obscure and makes no sense. It is very difficult to get in contact with her if you cannot attend her office hours. She reads off of the slides and tests on specific details she mentions one time in a lecture. She doesnt post slides with figures which makes it impossible to copy them down

Based on her lectures you would assume her course is a breeze,  although boring as she repeats examples and basic information. However, the questions on the midterms are not straight forward and are often about small details or material she decided to cover after the test. Long answer question are 1/2 pg but 20 marks. Not worth it! Avoid if you can
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I believe this was her first time teaching the course and it definitely shows. She is extremely confused, jumps around topics a lot and has zero flow. Asked questions on the midterm regarding minute details that weren't even mentioned in class, that being said midterms and final are super easy. Seems genuinely nice, just a terrible professor.

She is prejudice and if you are a person of colour stay away from this lecturer. She does not when her white liberal feminism is challenged and lack knowledge on many issues. Do not take her class! The people that liked her class were the ones who accepted her mediocrity.

Goes on tangents which take away from the overall learning time so we didn't cover everything. Heavily based on FEM content despite being a SOC course. Teaches her beliefs as fact and does not accept being challenged by students. Tests names of authors and menial facts, but exams and assignments are easy overall if you read and attend lectures.

She was pleasant to deal with and seemed like a very fair marker. She has a loud voice so it was easy to hear her speak from the back of the room. Couple tricky questions on exams and a LOT of reading. Overall, I enjoyed the course and it was useful. Lots of examples for course material to help you understand the concepts too. :)

Great prof who is very clear but not so helpful. Class is interesting and easy material however her midterm was tricky using the best answer m/c and heavy readings based. Do the readings, go to class, study lots and make sure you are aware of definitions versus stats and specifics. Enjoy the profs lectures and videos given they are very pertinent.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Enjoyed the lectures, she is a great lecturer, no papers, two midterm and final, just make sure you do the readings.

Very easy course. Louise is a great lecturer and gives you all the information you need to succeed. Lectures are long and breaks are short, so it can get pretty uncomfortable. Do not skip class, lots of things she talks about in class she will not post on blackboard. Lectures have a very feminist under tone, but that's not a big deal tbh.
Phenomenal professor. Best course do far!
Great prof, great course.

To put this debate to end , yes her lectures can be somewhat boring and long. No this course is not extremely difficult. And absolutely she turns it into a feminism class. Which in my opinion was disappointing because I felt I learned more about what women didn't do and what women couldn't be a part of than the actual history that occurred.
Such a good professor, really engaging. I dont know why so many people are bashing her here. If you study what she tells you to study it is an easy A Totally would take another class with her

Yes, she teaches the course from a feminist viewpoint. Women have always been suppressed in the fields of science and health care.  She's opening our minds to what a textbook doesn't mention. The content of the course is fairly straight-forward. Show up to class and do the readings, and you're golden. Very kind woman and cares about your success!

Louise is an amazing prof! I'm not sure what others mean when they say her lectures are dry. I never found her lectures boring, and the class was from 7-10. Her tests are not hard if you read her notes from class and the assigned chapters - there are absolutely no surprises. Always finishes class at least half an hour early. Overall, very friendly!
Not a nice person. Doesn't respond to most emails. And when she does respond, she gives you a sassy answer that is rude and insulting. Overall terrible prof, avoid if possible.

Super boring class. She starts the semester teaching "history of health care" then it because a women's rights course. Every lecture is all about women's roles. Classes are long and boring. Tests and midterms have random questions that aren't worth knowing. OH and you have to do volunteer hours. Overall, terrible prof. Great TA. Sucks for us Engs.

The readings are an insult to my intellectual capacity, they lack material that could keep ones mind stimulated. She doesn't respond to emails in a timely fashion. Her marking rubric only works if you write what is aligned with her views. Disappointing class. You can learn what she teaches by doing your own research.

The class lacked the critical component because this woman is not well versed in the topics. Contains problematics views on race and class. She doesn't email back in a timely manner and be careful if you aren't a speaker but a excellent writer she will try and charge you with  Plagiarism. Not a good lecturer.
Interesting material. Prof is engaged and attempts to engage class. Covers history and global information. Tests on historical facts. Posts slides with notes removed to blackboard.

I'm mortified that she can't  accept her students questioning and challenging her  arguments, that is the point of school and that is to think! She is an unfair marker, if you write from a perspective that is not aligned with hers,  god help you. If I listened to my friends, I would not have suffered through this class.

She repeats a lot of content. Her wording of assignments and exams is problematic, but as long as you know what she is looking for it is easy to produce. She teaches a feminism course yet a lot of the time some of the statements she makes and language she uses is problematic. Nice woman though.

Great prof! She was helpful and recommended good resources for my final paper. About 20% of her exams are based on the readings, if you want anything over a B to B+, you need the textbooks. Lectures were  interesting and well structured. Only complaint is thats sometimes she got defensive when students challenged her or raised questions.

i don't know why this prof has such bad reviews. I am taking her class on gender work and reproduction and i feel she really is a great prof. she always starts the class off with real world connections to the material we are covering, and i feel she really puts her heart and soul into prepping and teaching the course. Lectures can be a bit dry.

If I could turn the hands of time back, I would never have taken this class with a witch like her. I hate her with a passion. She works against her students, and is not helpful. She is RUDE and not a nice woman. Her wrinkled face will forever be etched in my mind as the worst person at Ottawa University. She should be removed from Ottawa University
Lectures are boring. Takes forever to answer emails, and is never available after office hours.

Fun lectures and interesting course material but marking scheme faulty as far as properly demonstrating knowledge of material. Unclear expectations and an inability to accept different interpretations of material.
Great prof!! Easy class if you take the time to study and take notes in class. great prof
I hated this class
One of my favourite professors at the University! Love attending her classes she is very helpful
really nice! easy class, she even took us out for beer and nachos at the end of the semester! i would definitely have her as a prof again!

This is probably the worst prof I have ever had at the university of Ottawa, her tests and midterms do not reflect coure material whatsoever. She asks random questions that aren't even releveant. Questions don't show if you understand the course. STAY CLEAR OF THIS PROF'!!!!!!!!!
This was one of my favourite classes taken while at the University of Ottawa. All the people in POL with negative comments probably failed and never went to class. Louise Rocks!!!!!!

This prof is so unprofessional. She was 5-15 minutes late for every class, late for office hours too, ridiculously late in handing back assignments, is not knowledgeable about subject matter, is not approachable, she should not be teaching at all. It was pretty infuriating even listening to her speak once I realized what a poor professor she wad.

Would have to agree with the other comments.  A genuinely nice person, however, this professor is not accountable for her choices or actions and instead blames others.  Takes an egregious and unprofessional amount of time to hand back grades and hand out assignments.  Changes her course outline at will.

Awful professor. Works against students. Always full of excuses. Takes FOREVER to get marks back. Unwilling to reconsider grades. Changes syllabus randomly. Too many assignments. Promises class time for group projects but gives none. Gives HUGE numbers of reserve readings (more than in the $70 of textbooks). Never answers questions directly.

Disorganized, late for class, does not attend office hours, condescending, bias, too much focus on group work, expectations unclear, does not touch textbooks, useless guest lectures, exams are ok but too long, not open to suggestions or constructive criticism.
